    {
      "id": "insight:9b38637b4c4d2e0d",
      "properties": {
        "confidence": 0.7,
        "grounded": true,
        "text": "In this episode, I\u2019m going to build a grounded map: what\u2019s real, what\u2019s uncertain, and what you can do without turning your life into an optimization project."
      },
      "type": "Insight"
    },
    {
      "id": "insight:de1876082b36b0d4",
      "properties": {
        "confidence": 0.7,
        "grounded": true,
        "text": "Alex Morgan: Where the field is right now."
      },
      "type": "Insight"
    },
    {
      "id": "insight:eee0c952d51f4059",
      "properties": {
        "confidence": 0.7,
        "grounded": true,
        "text": "Alex Morgan: The second step is to separate interventions that improve fundamentals from interventions that just create the feeling of progress."
      },
      "type": "Insight"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:65c95a0310373c91",
      "properties": {
        "speaker": "Speaker 1",
        "text": "Alex Morgan: The most useful starting point is to ask what problem you\u2019re trying to solve, and what constraints you can\u2019t wish away: time, stress, sleep, money, and attention."
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:f7e2889773e82c16",
      "properties": {
        "speaker": "Speaker 1",
        "text": "Alex Morgan: A good heuristic is to prefer boring things that compound: regular sleep timing, strength, protein, daylight, and social stability."
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:1ea26d5ea166b6ae",
      "properties": {
        "speaker": "Speaker 1",
        "text": "Alex Morgan: If a protocol only works when life is perfect, it is not a protocol; it is a performance."
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    }
  ],
